jpg";s:5:"width";i:800;s:6:"height";i:800;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/618541330049299725/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:47:{i:0;s:49:"Woman uses makeup mirror to help fix garage door.";i:1;s:91:"Garage door wont close using the remote but closes if you hold down the button on the wall.";i:2;s:136:"If the beam is broken or the sensors are misaligned the sensor lights will go off and subsequently tell the operator not close the door.";i:3;s:127:"The garage door may attempt to go down but will come right back up and the overhead light on the garage door opener will blink.";i:4;s:51:"This also disables any remotes or wireless keypads.";i:5;s:55:"Why will my garage door open but not close with remote.";i:6;s:143:"The problem is either due to a blocked path between the sensors dirty eyes loose wires at the sensors or at the motor head or just bad sensors.";i:7;s:64:"The transmitters remotes will not work to close the garage door.";i:8;s:147:"When the garage door doesnt budge at all when the remote or wall switch pressed its almost certain the power source has been disrupted in some way.";i:9;s:104:"As with many such problems the most common problem is the simplest onethe motor unit has been unplugged.";i:10;s:33:"Thanks to everyone on this forum.";i:11;s:127:"Had a 15 year old Craftsman 12 HP garage door opener that would open with remote and panel but would not close with the remote.";i:12;s:80:"I noticed that the bulb on the garage opener turned on when it opened or closed.";i:13;s:77:"The garage door would only go down using the remote once the bulb turned off.";i:14;s:213:"My Garage Door Will Open But Not Close With Remote Posted on May 16 2020 by Bandi Ruma Thieves out of your garage top 10 reasons your garage door won t garage door not opening 9 best smart garage door opener 2020.";i:15;s:94:"The problem could be a defect in the remotes or a degradation of the receiver circuit or both.";i:16;s:17:"Heres what to do.";i:17;s:52:"First make sure that the remote batteries are fresh.";i:18;s:70:"Use a battery tester not just a voltmeter or just replace the battery.";i:19;s:103:"Double check that the receiver antenna wire if any is not mangled and has a good connection internally.";i:20;s:51:"Remove the wires from the back of the door control.";i:21;s:25:"Test the remote controls.";i:22;s:53:"If remote controls do not work then replace the wire.";i:23;s:69:"If remote controls work reconnect the wires to door control and test.";i:24;s:85:"If remote controls continue to work then there was a loose connection with the wires.";i:25;s:56:"If remote controls do not work replace the door control.";i:26;s:78:"When the remote will not close the door try holding the wall button depressed.";i:27;s:32:"This overides the safety system.";i:28;s:42:"If this works look to your safety sensors.";i:29;s:108:"One of the most common reasons that the garage door may not close is because the lock-out button is engaged.";i:30;s:86:"This button is to prevent the door from opening or closing using the hand-held remote.";i:31;s:82:"To determine if this is the issue press the garage door button on the garage wall.";i:32;s:88:"The garage door not closing is one of the earliest signs of garage door sensor problems.";i:33;s:106:"If the garage door opens but fails to close completely then you should consider checking the door sensors.";i:34;s:122:"Safety sensors are located near the bottom of the door track on both sides that require a clear line of view between them.";i:35;s:313:"Garage door troubleshooting having problems with your garage door garage door not opening 9 legacy 850 garage door opener mon garage door problems 5 Reasons Your Garage Door Won T Close All Pro RepairGarage Door Will Not Close All The Way Leaves Gap At Bottom15 Reasons Why Your Garage Door Won T Open Or Close11.";i:36;s:89:"My Chamberlain garage door opener does not close the door properly when using the remote.";i:37;s:94:"I have to hold down the button inside the garage to get it to close the door all the way down.";i:38;s:99:"As youd expect it works fine when opening the door using either a remote or by pressing the button.";i:39;s:117:"If your garage door opens ok but wont close then its possible the safety reversing sensors are not correctly aligned.";i:40;s:67:"Dont just assume that if the path is clear that the sensors are ok.";i:41;s:42:"This problem bugged me for several months.";i:42;s:75:"Hopefully after you read this you wont have the same problem in the future.";i:43;s:148:"When you see your garage door opener lights flashing and the garage door will not close it could be the safety reversing sensors or the LOCK button.";i:44;s:75:"If there is a safety reversing sensor issue the main lights flash 10 times.";i:45;s:39:"Start with aligning the safety sensors.";i:46;s:111:"You can close the garage door by pressing and holding the door control push bar until down travel is completed.";}}